## 2026-01-17 00:45 - Voice Recognition Testing Complete

### Actions
- Tested whisper server with short Italian audio (12.7s): RTF 0.356x (2.8x real-time)
- Tested whisper server with long English video (8m47s): RTF 0.688x (1.5x real-time)
- Identified YOLO agent's performance estimate was based on GPU benchmarks, not CPU
- Corrected performance expectations in model_registry.yaml (25x → 2.8x)
- Verified 64 threads optimal; 96 threads causes NUMA contention

### Files Updated
- progress/2026-01/2026-01-16.md - Added verified performance sections
- handoffs/active/voice_recognition_setup.md - Corrected RTF expectations, added test results
- orchestration/model_registry.yaml - Fixed throughput from 25.0 to 2.8

### Key Finding
faster-whisper large-v3-turbo on CPU int8 achieves ~2.8x real-time (RTF 0.35x), not 25x as originally estimated. The 25x figure was based on GPU fp16 benchmarks.

## 2026-01-20 - LightOnOCR-2 Document Formalizer Setup

### Actions
- Downloaded LightOnOCR-2-1B-bbox model to /mnt/raid0/llm/hf/ (1.9GB)
- Installed dependencies: transformers 5.0.0.dev0 (from source), pillow, pypdfium2, fastapi, uvicorn, accelerate
- Verified model loads successfully: Mistral3ForConditionalGeneration, 1.16B params, 12.3s load time
- Discovered architecture: Pixtral vision encoder + Qwen3 text backbone (not custom VLM)
- Fixed transformers 5.0 API changes: AutoModelForImageTextToText, dtype= not torch_dtype=
- Enhanced handoff with tested code templates and YOLO agent task prompt
- Note: torchvision skipped due to version mismatch with torch 2.9.1

### Files Updated
- handoffs/active/lighton_ocr_integration.md - Enhanced with verified code templates
- progress/2026-01/2026-01-20.md - Added session 2 details
- progress/INDEX.md - Updated summary

### Key Finding
LightOnOCR-2 is NOT a custom architecture - it's Mistral3-based (Pixtral + Qwen3). Requires transformers 5.0+ from source. Model loading verified at 12.3s on EPYC 9655.

