  - Result: tree not yet a net win — overhead exceeds benefit of alternative path discovery
  - Root cause: get_best_path() returns draft-optimal path, not greedy — causes path 0 to underperform linear
  - Critical next step: return greedy path as slot.drafted to guarantee no regression vs linear
  - Files: common/common.h, common/common.cpp, tools/server/server-context.cpp
  - Data: epyc-inference-research/data/tree_speculation/server_sweep_20260314_*.csv
  - Branch: feature/tree-speculation off production-consolidated-v2

2026-03-14 tree-speculation greedy path fix
  - Added get_greedy_path() to speculation_tree struct (follows primary/top-1 children)
  - Changed draft() to return get_greedy_path() instead of get_best_path()
  - Guarantees path 0 never worse than linear — tree can only improve via alt path wins
  - Impact: minimal on 32B pair (374/502 → 375/503 — paths already agree ~99% of the time)
  - Root cause of regression is construction overhead, not path selection
  - Round-level: tree gets +21% more accepted/round (2.74 vs 2.26) but overhead offsets gain
