## 2026-03-30/31 — Continuation Session: AR-1, RI-7, Bug Fixes

### Tasks Completed
- AR-1: Debug suite baseline (105 questions, 3-way eval). Direct 57.3%, REPL 43.1%, Architect 52.4%. Baseline written to autopilot_baseline.yaml.
- RI-7: A/B test Phase 4 (70 questions/arm). All differences NS (p>0.4). Enforce mode neither helps nor hurts.
- Bug fix: features().factual_risk_mode AttributeError in routing.py → replaced with get_mode()
- Bug fix: Added ORCHESTRATOR_FACTUAL_RISK_MODE env var override to factual_risk.py
- Bug discovery: Health probe full: prefix issue → logged as LC-5
- Updated routing-and-optimization-index.md (AR-1 ✅, RI-7 ✅, LC-5 added)
- Created progress/2026-03/2026-03-30.md

### Key Findings
- Tools hurt more than help in 3-way eval (24 hurt vs 9 helped) — REPL overhead on simple questions
- Architect comparable to direct despite higher cost
- Factual risk enforce mode has no measurable effect at n=70/arm (underpowered)
- Oracle best-of-3 ceiling estimated ~65-75% (vs 57.3% best single role)

### Decisions
- AR-3 autopilot: user will run manually with --tui (no --no-controller, no --max-trials)
- Saved feedback: always use --tui, autopilot must optimize full production flow
